stylometry: The tradeoff discussed in the problem can be a product of supply and demand.  If you have a product or service that is in high demand it would make sense to order more than what is needed to store them at your facility in order to have them as soon as they are needed.  The costs incurred for holding these materials is okay because the products are being turned over very rapidly.  If the supply is not in demand and you are holding them at your facility, the holding costs are costing you money just to hold on to them until you possibly sell them . There is a chance you might not even sell them.  SO the tradeoff between production costs and holding costs are either customer service in the amount of time needed to get the product or the quality of the product might not be as good if the item has sit in your warehouse for a period of time.
